          <mj-text>
            <h4>More Summer Music Happenings</h4>

            <p>This summer marks our 10th year broadcasting live from RockyGrass [[ link ]], featuring Del McCoury Band, Sam Bush Bluegrass Band, Earls of Leicester, Infamous Stringdusters and many more, July 28-30th in Lyons.
              <br><br>
              In addition to our regular complete live stream of the festival via <a href="http://kgnu.org">KGNU.org</a> and <a href="http://www.afterfm.com/index.cfm/fuseaction/rocky.grass">AfterFM.com </a>, we’ll be broadcasting more of the music from the festival over our airwaves than ever before, We hope you’ll join us at the festival or through our broadcast for this exciting Colorado music event, now in its 45th year.
              <br><br>
              The following weekend, August 4-6, KGNU will also provide an AfterFM live stream of the <a href="http://arisefestival.com/">Arise Music Festival</a>. Check in with our <a href="http://www.afterfm.com/index.cfm/fuseaction/content.byTag/tagID/93">streaming page</a> for updates on our streaming schedule as the festival approaches.
              <br><br>
              These are only a few of the music-related events KGNU will be involved in this summer, so check out our <a href="http://www.afterfm.com/index.cfm/fuseaction/content.kgnuPresentsListings/showing/1">complete list</a> of KGNU concerts and outreach events in the coming months.</p>

              <strong>KGNU’s Annual CD and Record Sale - Aug 27th</strong>

<p>KGNU’s 2017 Record and CD Sale is happening Sun 8/27 and Fri 9/1 at our Denver home at 700 Kalamath St. Donate those unwanted records and CDs now, and pick up some new discoveries at the sale. See you there! Click <a href="http://kgnu.org/cgi-bin/moreinfo.py?Notice=1493482022">here</a> for more info.</p>

            </mj-text>
          </mj-column>
        </mj-section>

